  "prompt": "Do I have to shave during a passport appointment?",
  "response": "You do **not** have to shave for your passport appointment. However, there are specific guidelines regarding facial hair that you should follow to ensure your passport photo is accepted:\n\n### **Facial Hair Guidelines for Passport Photos:**\n\n1. **Clear Visibility:** \n   - **Beard or Goatee:** Allowed, but must not obscure the edges of your face or cover your facial features. Ensure your entire face, including your hairline and ears, is clearly visible.\n   - **Mustache:** Permitted as long as it doesn\u2019t cover your upper lip and mouth area.\n   \n2. **Even Lighting and Contrast:**\n   - Ensure that any facial hair doesn't cast shadows on your face, which could obscure your features.\n\n3. **Neutral Expression:**\n   - Maintain a natural, neutral expression with both eyes open. Facial hair should not alter your expression.\n\n4. **No Obstructions:**\n   - Avoid using products that add volume or texture that might create shadows or distort your facial features.\n\n### **Additional Passport Photo Tips:**\n\n- **Background:** Use a plain white or off-white background without any patterns or shadows.\n- **Head Position:** Face the camera directly with your head centered and straight.\n- **Glasses:** If you normally wear glasses, ensure there is no glare, and your eyes are fully visible. Remove non-prescription glasses if possible.\n- **Headgear:** Only wear headgear for religious purposes, and it must not obscure any part of your face.\n\n### **Recommendations:**\n\n- **Professional Photography:** Consider getting your photo taken by a professional photographer who is familiar with passport photo requirements.\n- **Review Guidelines:** Always check the latest passport photo requirements from the official [U.S. Department of State website](https://travel.state.gov/content/travel/en/passports/how-apply/photos.html) or the relevant authority in your country to ensure compliance.\n- **Bring a Sample:** If you're uncertain, bring an example of an acceptable photo to your appointment or consult with the passport agency beforehand.\n\nBy following these guidelines, you can ensure that your facial hair does not interfere with the approval of your passport application. Shaving is optional and based on your personal preference, as long as your photo meets all necessary criteria.",
